Kilimani Residents held a get together fundraising dinner last weekend at Monikos Club where they addressed their concerns and highlighted their problems and challenges as a community with an aim of how to solve them.Through the Kilimani Project Foundation Chairperson Ir ng Houghton the residents were able to raise their concerns which mainly included noise pollution, insecurity, congestion etc to the Nairobi Deputy Governor Jonathan Mueke who was the Chief Guest.Among other notables at the dinner event were Kamukunji MP Hon. Yusuf Hassan, Eastleigh Businessman Ahmed Mohamed, Kiko Romeo's Ann McCreath and Vivo Energy Executive Executive Andrew Waititu among others.